 ## Security Model
 
-### LAN-Only Binding
+**LAN-only binding.** Daemon binds `127.0.0.1` by default. Remote access is deferred to a later slice.
 
-- Daemon binds to `127.0.0.1` by default
-- Configurable via `ZEND_BIND_HOST` environment variable
-- Port configurable via `ZEND_BIND_PORT` (default: 8080)
+**Capability scoping.** `observe` grants read access; `control` is required for mining commands. An observer client cannot issue control commands.
 
-### Capability Scoping
+**Token replay prevention ‚Äî gap.** `store.py` defines `token_used: bool = False` on `GatewayPairing` but no code path sets it to `True` after a pairing token is consumed. This must be closed before production.
 
-- `observe`: Read status, health, events
-- `control`: Issue mining commands (start/stop/set_mode)
+**No mining on client.** `no_local_hashing_audit.sh` confirms no mining code runs in the client HTML/JS. Actual hashing happens on home-miner hardware only.
 
-### Token Replay Prevention
-
-**Status:** Defined but not enforced.
-
-The `store.py` defines `token_used=False` on pairing records, but no code path sets this to `True` after use. This must be addressed in genesis plan 003.
